On a cold December day in 2009, the mystery that still captivates America began.

Susan Powell was a regular woman. She was a wife, a mother, a co-worker, and church-goer.

She was also a victim, but of just what crime, no one can say with certainty.

She disappeared on a cold December night nearly 10 years ago. Her body has never been found.

KSL’s Dave Cawley has spent the last three years examining tens of thousands of documents and recordings relating to the case of Susan Powell. He's uncovered evidence that has never before been seen or heard publicly -- information that brings this haunting cold case into a whole new light, many times through the words of those involved.

Join Cold as we take a look inside the mind of Josh Powell, inside this fractured family, and inside this fateful marriage.

Why did Josh kill in cold blood? Why was he was never charged with a crime? And why did Susan never leave?

We’ve strived to answer these questions in this multi-part podcast, Cold.
